sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K669006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Allows the measurement of the CBP promoter activity
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Chitooligosaccharide-binding protein (CBP) is a cytoplasmatic protein that regulates the transcriptional activity of the ChiS sensor.
When chitin is present in the external media, CBP binds with GlcNAc oligomers (chitin degradation products) and liberates the sensor for the up-regulation of the chitinolitic degradation cascade in Vibrio fischeri ES114.
